---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Designing for Scalability: HLD Guide">
    <div class="py-12">
        <article class="max-w-3xl">
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold gradient-text mb-4">Designing for Scalability: HLD Guide</h1>
            <div class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">Published on June 10, 2026</div>
            <div class="flex gap-2 mb-8 flex-wrap">
                <span class="bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded">System Design</span>
                <span class="bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded">Architecture</span>
            </div>

            <section class="space-y-6">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">The Scalability Pyramid</h2>
                <p>Scalability is built in layers: single machine limits, vertical scaling, horizontal scaling, and eventually distributed systems.</p>
                
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Stateless Services</h2>
                <p>Design services to be stateless when possible. Store state externally to allow horizontal scaling without coordination.</p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Database Sharding</h2>
                <p>As data grows, partition it across multiple databases using sharding strategies that minimize cross-shard queries.</p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Caching and CDN</h2>
                <p>Reduce database load with caching layers and distribute content globally using CDNs for better latency.</p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Async Processing</h2>
                <p>Use message queues for async processing to decouple services and handle traffic spikes gracefully.</p>
            </section>

            <a href="/blog" class="inline-block mt-12 text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700 font-medium">← Back to Blog</a>
        </article>
    </div>
</MainLayout>
